c graph-cut-v0 one-edge-cut-rejected
c Variables r_{i,v} mean vertex v is reachable from s in at most i steps after
c removing the listed cut edge (s,a). Vertex order is s,a,b,t and depths are
c 0..3, so var = 4*i + vertex_index + 1.
c The remaining undirected edges are (a,t), (s,b), and (b,t). The final clause
c asserts !r_{3,t}, contradicting the remaining path s-b-t.
